I‚Äôve been playing this game since 2017 and have seen it go from a mediocre laggy awful game to a decently presentable game. I‚Äôve won a few games and lost some. I really like the vehicles in the game and they are very easy to control. A little glitchy sometimes but not bad. The guns are really good and the graphics are fantastic. When you are in the waiting lobby the songs that play are super cringy but that‚Äôs really not an issue. The main things I hate about the game is when you come up to a person and start shooting them they start jumping around like they are on a trampoline and one of their teammates kills you. I‚Äôve had this happen to me so many times and it‚Äôs extremely unrealistic to even jump like that. I get it, it‚Äôs a game but the jump feature is so terrible and unrealistic it just doesn‚Äôt make any sense. One game I played not long ago I was playing with one of my friends and we were two of four people left. We were in a hotel and the other two people were coming up, so we waited for them to come in the door. Then the game completely froze and we couldn‚Äôt move. Came back about 30 seconds later and we were both dead and the game was over. It didn‚Äôt make any sense. We had perfect signal and we both had iPads which were fully suitable to play this game. I had this happen to me about 5 times but never with someone else. Definitely something that needs to be looked at. I also get a laugh at the people who spend large amounts of money on this game because in order to get perks in this game you need to spend quite a bit of money. I kept getting killed by people with an ‚Äúakm deep freeze‚Äù and if I remember correctly that gun skin costed 20 dollars. Just seemed ridiculous to buy a skin for a mediocre gun in an average FPS game. At least there are less bots in this game which make it better than pubg and the gameplay is so much better than pubg and your character actually looks more realistic than in pubg, where the map looks like it was designed in 2002. Overall not a bad game but there are some things that should be addressed.
